  "content": [
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "What is HTML Datalist?"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "value": "The <datalist> element provides a list of predefined options for an input field, offering auto-suggestions as the user types."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Basic Syntax"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "language": "html",
      "value": "<input list=\"browsers\">\n<datalist id=\"browsers\">\n  <option value=\"Chrome\">\n  <option value=\"Firefox\">\n  <option value=\"Edge\">\n</datalist>"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "How it Works"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "value": "The input field uses the list attribute to connect with the datalist. As the user types, matching options are shown as suggestions."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Example with Labels"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "language": "html",
      "value": "<label for=\"browser\">Choose browser:</label>\n<input id=\"browser\" list=\"browsers\">\n<datalist id=\"browsers\">\n  <option value=\"Chrome\">\n  <option value=\"Safari\">\n</datalist>"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Using with Different Input Types"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "language": "html",
      "value": "<input type=\"text\" list=\"cities\">\n<datalist id=\"cities\">\n  <option value=\"Chennai\">\n  <option value=\"Delhi\">\n</datalist>"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Advantages"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "value": [
        "**Provides auto-suggestions**",
        "**Improves user experience**",
        "**Allows custom input beyond suggestions**",
        "**Easy to implement without JavaScript**"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Limitations"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "value": [
        "**Limited styling options**",
        "**Browser support variations (older browsers)**",
        "**No strict validation (user can enter any value)**"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Best Practices"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "value": [
        "**Use datalist for suggestions, not strict selection**",
        "**Provide meaningful options**",
        "**Combine with validation if needed**",
        "**Use labels for accessibility**"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Common Mistakes"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "value": [
        "**Forgetting to link input with datalist (list attribute)**",
        "**Expecting datalist to enforce validation**",
        "**Overloading with too many options**",
        "**Missing labels for inputs**"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Conclusion"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "value": "HTML datalist enhances input fields with suggestions, improving usability while keeping flexibility for user input."
    }
